Humbucker plus Piezo run into an overdriven Deluxe Reverb is pure honey ... Sweet guitar ... Slight ‘scratches’, barely visible, from normal use ... A beautiful instrument! NO INTERNATIONAL SHIPPING!! I got burned badly last year by ab Australian buyer, lost over 50% of my entire sale. Never again! NO INTERNATIONAL SHIPPING!! From Eastwood site: Airline® Guitars were made in the USA from 1958-68 by VALCO and sold through Montgomery Ward. VALCO also made National and SUPRO brands. The original Folkstar resonator guitar did not have pickups, this modern professional model adds two pickups and a blend switch for versatile stage use.
